          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The radioactivity of the residual nuclei in",
                "the activated foils was measured nondestructively",
                "using a HPGe gamma-ray detector with 70% efficiency",
                "relative to a (3\"x3\") NaI detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two different sets of stacks were",
                "irradiated to cover the energy range from the",
                "respective threshold for each reaction up to 40 MeV.",
                "Each stack was made of several groups of targets;",
                "natMo (99.999% and 50 microm thickness) as the main",
                "target foils, natCu (99.98% and 125 microm thickness)",
                "were used as monitor foils that acted also as beam",
                "degraders and natAl",
                " (99.999% and 50,100 microm thickness) as catcher",
                "foils, all foils were supplied by Goodfellow,",
                "Cambridge, UK. The set of foils was pressed together",
                "to avoid air gaps between them, which could have",
                "influence on the vacuum and particles stopping. The",
                "proton energy degradation along the stack was",
                "determined using the computer program SRIM-2003",
                "assuming the incident energy was 40 MeV.",
                "Stack 1: 39.4 - 19 MeV; Stack 2: 20.3 - 0 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
